I thought so too, so I'm setting it in lib/tempest to "cirros", like for the image_ssh_user:
https://review.opendev.org/#/c/682902/4/lib/tempest

It might prove to be an issue if the user is using a non-cirros image for testing and configured only image_ssh_user - atm the image_alt_ssh_user will be set to "cirros" by Devstack, regardless of the image used, in the same way as image_ssh_user is being set. That would mean the user has to configure the second variable as well.

I can keep the image_ssh_user hardcoded to cirros (so leave it unchanged), but set the image_alt_ssh_user to the image_ssh_user value to prevent this from happening.

So instead of:
iniset $TEMPEST_CONFIG validation image_ssh_user ${DEFAULT_INSTANCE_USER:-cirros}
iniset $TEMPEST_CONFIG validation image_alt_ssh_user ${DEFAULT_INSTANCE_ALT_USER:-cirros}

do it like this:
iniset $TEMPEST_CONFIG validation image_ssh_user ${DEFAULT_INSTANCE_USER:-cirros}
iniset $TEMPEST_CONFIG validation image_alt_ssh_user ${DEFAULT_INSTANCE_ALT_USER:-$DEFAULT_INSTANCE_USER}

Is that what you had in mind?

